==English==
===Adjective===
'''1. Used to describe a person, object, or action that is unusually dangerous, janky, and/or impressive. Example: Kirchart's fall down the tower rails was "gnar."'''

'''2. Used to describe a person that seems to have no fear of personal destruction. Example: Chris Cole is so "gnar."'''
